50|$|In Lahaul the glum {{is pressed}} out by hand instead of by filtering, {{yielding}} a rather <b>cloudy</b> <b>drink.</b> The residue of malt can be pressed through a strainer and then mixed with water or milk {{and used in}} baking bread or cakes.|$|E
50|$|Sake {{is usually}} {{filtered}} to remove grain solids left behind after the fermentation process. Nigori sake is filtered using a broader mesh, {{resulting in the}} permeating of fine rice particles and a far <b>cloudier</b> <b>drink.</b>|$|R

